message.content: If Harmony makes a notepad with 5 sheets of paper, then writing 10 notes per day would mean that each sheet can be used for 2 days (10 notes / 5 sheets = 2). Since the sheets are stapled together, they should last for at least as long as the weakest sheet. Assuming that the paper is strong enough to withstand being written on for two days in a row, then one notepad would last for 2 days x 5 sheets = 10 days. However, if the paper is not strong enough to endure being written on for two consecutive days, then it may not last the full ten days.
